shit: 3:3: warning: A one-operand test is the nonempty-string test, write it with -n to read clearer.
     3 |  [ "(" ]; echo "paren_single=$?"
       |    ^~~ here.
shit: 4:3: warning: A one-operand test is the nonempty-string test, write it with -n to read clearer.
     4 |  [ ")" ]; echo "rparen_single=$?"
       |    ^~~ here.
shit: 13:15: warning: A test with -a or -o is obsolescent, join two tests with && or || instead.
    13 |  [ \( a = a \) -a -n x ]; echo "group_and=$?"
       |                ^~ here.
shit: 13:21: warning: The operand is a literal, so this -n test is constant, test a variable or drop the check.
    13 |  [ \( a = a \) -a -n x ]; echo "group_and=$?"
       |                      ^~ here.
